<h2>Can Someone with a PhD Be a Research Assistant?</h2>
<ul>
<li>A <b>Research Assistant</b> (Arş. Gör.) is academic personnel at universities, typically tenured, who is continuing or has completed graduate studies and supports education and teaching activities.</li>
<li>A research assistant who has completed their doctorate can still remain in the <b>Research Assistant</b> position. However, the next natural step in their career is to meet the requirements for an appointment to the <b>Assistant Professor</b> (Dr. Öğretim Üyesi) position.</li>
<li>A Research Assistant who has finished their PhD can also choose to enhance their academic experience at a different institution by applying for the <b>Postdoctoral Researcher (Postdoc)</b> positions or scholarships mentioned above.</li>
</ul>
</div>
