<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What documents are required for postdoctoral research in Turkey?</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>The following documents are generally required for postdoctoral research in Turkey:</li>
<li>PhD diploma</li>
<li>Research proposal</li>
<li>Letters of reference</li>
<li>Passport and visa documents</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the research fields at Turkish universities?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Universities in Turkey offer research opportunities in many fields, such as engineering, natural sciences, social sciences, and health sciences. For example, ODTÜ is strong in engineering, while Boğaziçi Üniversitesi is strong in social sciences.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How long does postdoctoral research take?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The duration of postdoctoral research typically ranges from 1-3 years, depending on the project. However, this period may vary according to the scope and requirements of the research.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How can international students get a work permit in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students can obtain a work permit under certain conditions during their studies. This permit is issued along with the student visa and is generally limited to 20 hours of work per week.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-05-17T11:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:52:16Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'postdoctoral-research-opportunities-in-turkey' );
