<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Foire Aux Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quels sont les documents requis pour une recherche postdoctorale en Turquie ?</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Pour effectuer une recherche postdoctorale en Turquie, les documents suivants sont généralement requis :</li>
<li>Diplôme de doctorat</li>
<li>Projet de recherche</li>
<li>Lettres de recommandation</li>
<li>Passeport et documents de visa</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quels sont les domaines de recherche des universités en Turquie ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les universités en Turquie offrent des possibilités de recherche dans de nombreux domaines tels que l&#8217;ingénierie, les sciences naturelles, les sciences sociales et les sciences de la santé. Par exemple, ODTÜ est réputée dans le domaine de l&#8217;ingénierie, tandis que l&#8217;Université de Boğaziçi est forte en sciences sociales.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quelle est la durée d&#8217;une recherche postdoctorale ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">La durée d&#8217;une recherche postdoctorale varie généralement entre 1 et 3 ans, en fonction du projet. Cependant, cette durée peut varier en fonction de l&#8217;envergure et des exigences de la recherche.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Comment les étudiants internationaux peuvent-ils obtenir un permis de travail en Turquie ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les étudiants internationaux peuvent obtenir un permis de travail sous certaines conditions pendant leurs études. Ce permis est accordé avec le visa étudiant et est généralement limité à 20 heures de travail par semaine.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-03-20T04:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-14T15:45:24Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'fr' AND "slug" = 'opportunites-de-recherche-postdoctorale-en-turquie' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Develop Your Scientific Thinking Skills in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","description":"Explore educational opportunities in Turkey! Check out our guide to developing your scientific thinking and critical analysis skills.","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Develop Your Scientific Thinking Skills in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Explore educational opportunities in Turkey! Check out our guide to developing your scientific thinking and critical analysis skills.","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Develop Your Scientific Thinking Skills in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Explore educational opportunities in Turkey! Check out our guide to developing your scientific thinking and critical analysis skills.","canonicalPath":"/en/develop-your-scientific-thinking-skills-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-bilimsel-dusunme-becerileri/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/develop-your-scientific-thinking-skills-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/kembangkan-keterampilan-berpikir-ilmiah-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/developper-des-competences-en-pensee-scientifique-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/develop-your-scientific-thinking-skills-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/develop-your-scientific-thinking-skills-in-turkey/","name":"Develop Your Scientific Thinking Skills in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-17T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-17T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Develop Your Scientific Thinking Skills in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-17T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-17T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Explore educational opportunities in Turkey! Check out our guide to developing your scientific thinking and critical analysis skills.","name":"Develop Your Scientific Thinking Skills in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/develop-your-scientific-thinking-skills-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/develop-your-scientific-thinking-skills-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/develop-your-scientific-thinking-skills-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="JlqpRe"><span class="JCzEY tNxQIb"><span class="CSkcDe">What are scientific thinking skills?</span></span></h2>
<p>Scientific thinking skills are the <strong>mental abilities</strong> that enable an individual to reason based on scientific methods, enhancing their capacity to solve problems, acquire knowledge, and understand the events around them.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Basic Process Skills (Data Collection)</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Observation:</strong> <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkce-ogrenirken-coklu-duyu-kullanimi/" data-type="post" data-id="9327">Collecting data through the senses</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Classification:</strong> Grouping objects based on common characteristics.</li>
<li><strong>Measurement:</strong> Obtaining numerical data.</li>
<li><strong>Predicting:</strong> Foreseeing an outcome based on data.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Integrated Process Skills (Reasoning and Inference)</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Formulating a Hypothesis:</strong> Proposing testable, temporary solutions (assumptions).</li>
<li><strong>Identifying/Controlling Variables:</strong> Recognizing and managing factors that affect the outcome.</li>
<li><strong>Designing an Experiment:</strong> Creating a systematic plan to test the hypothesis.</li>
<li><strong>Interpreting Data:</strong> Analyzing collected information to reach a conclusion.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What are the methods of scientific thinking?</h2>
<p>The scientific method is a <strong>step-by-step systematic process</strong> used by scientists to understand, explain, and solve problems and phenomena in the universe in a systematic, logical, and objective way. This method is primarily based on <strong>observation</strong> and <strong>experimentation</strong>.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Identifying the Problem (Asking a Question)</h3>
<p>Every scientific process begins with a clear and concise question that needs a solution. The topic to be investigated or a <strong>contradiction/problem in an observation</strong> is defined.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><em>Example:</em> &#8220;Why is plant X growing slower than the others?&#8221;</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Observation and Data Collection</h3>
<p>Previous studies related to the problem are reviewed (<strong>Literature Review</strong>), and new, detailed observations are made.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Quantitative Observation:</strong> Objective observations made with measurement tools (numerical).</li>
<li><strong>Qualitative Observation:</strong> Subjective observations made with sensory organs.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Formulating a Hypothesis</h3>
<p>Based on the collected data, a temporary, <strong>testable</strong>, and logical explanation (assumption) for the problem is proposed. A good hypothesis usually states the relationship between two or more variables.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><em>Example:</em> &#8220;If plant X is given more sunlight, its growth rate will increase.&#8221;</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">4. Making a Prediction</h3>
<p>The <strong>expected outcome</strong> if the hypothesis is correct is logically stated (Deduction).</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><em>Example:</em> &#8220;If the hypothesis is correct, when we place plant X in bright light, its height will be greater than the other group&#8217;s within a month.&#8221;</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">5. Designing and Conducting a Controlled Experiment</h3>
<p>A systematic experiment is planned and conducted to test the prediction.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Controlled Experiment:</strong> A setup where all factors (control variables) are kept constant except for the one being tested (the independent variable). It typically uses an <strong>experimental group</strong> (where the variable is applied) and a <strong>control group</strong> (kept under normal conditions).</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">6. Analyzing Data and Drawing Conclusions</h3>
<p>The data (measurements) obtained from the experiment are analyzed. The results are then stated as either <strong>supporting</strong> or <strong>refuting</strong> the hypothesis.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>If the Hypothesis is Supported:</strong> Broader theories begin to be formulated.</li>
<li><strong>If the Hypothesis is Refuted:</strong> The process returns to the initial hypothesis, and a new one is formulated (Feedback Loop).</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">7. Sharing and Replicating Results</h3>
<p>The findings are shared through scientific publications. This allows other scientists to repeat the same experiment (<strong>Reproducibility</strong>) and either confirm or refute the results.</p>
<p>All these steps create a cycle that ensures knowledge is developed objectively, systematically, and continuously. Hypotheses supported by new and very strong evidence can eventually become a <strong>Theory</strong>, while generalizations accepted as unchangeable and expressible mathematically can become a <strong>Law</strong>.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to Develop Thinking Skills?</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Improving Critical Thinking</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Questioning:</strong> When reading news or learning information, instead of accepting it immediately, ask yourself, <strong>&#8220;What is the author&#8217;s evidence?&#8221;</strong> and <strong>&#8220;Could there be another explanation for this situation?&#8221;</strong></li>
<li><strong>Awareness of Bias:</strong> When making a decision or having a discussion, pause and think, <strong>&#8220;How are my personal beliefs or feelings influencing this decision?&#8221;</strong> This helps you be more objective.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Improving Analytical Thinking</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Breaking it Down:</strong> Break down a <strong>large project</strong> that seems difficult to start into <strong>small, sequential steps</strong> (Phase 1, Phase 2, etc.). This makes the solution more systematic.</li>
<li><strong>Brain Games:</strong> Regularly solve puzzles like <strong>Chess</strong>, <strong>Sudoku</strong>, or <strong>logic puzzles</strong>. This improves your planning ability and the speed at which you establish cause-and-effect relationships.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Improving Creative Thinking</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Brainstorming:</strong> When looking for a solution to a problem, write down all the possibilities that come to mind, including the <strong>most seemingly illogical ideas</strong> at first. Focus on generating a large number of ideas without judgment.</li>
<li><strong>Different Perspectives:</strong> Try to imagine a situation you&#8217;re facing from the perspective of someone who isn&#8217;t an expert on the topic or is from a completely different profession (like an artist or a child). This develops your <strong>mental flexibility</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What are higher-order thinking skills?</h2>
<p>Higher-order thinking skills (HOTS) go beyond simply memorizing information; they are the ability to use and analyze it in complex ways to produce new outcomes.</p>
<p>These skills are generally categorized under three main headings:</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Critical Thinking</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Definition:</strong> The <strong>purposeful and rational</strong> evaluation of information, an argument, or a situation based on evidence.</li>
<li><strong>Key Actions:</strong> <strong>Analyzing</strong> evidence, <strong>questioning</strong> the reliability of information, and identifying <strong>biases</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Creative Thinking</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Definition:</strong> The ability to find <strong>original, new, and unconventional</strong> solutions to problems or situations.</li>
<li><strong>Key Actions:</strong> <strong>Synthesizing</strong> different ideas and generating numerous <strong>alternatives</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Metacognitive Thinking</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Definition:</strong> An individual&#8217;s ability to <strong>manage their own thinking and learning processes</strong> and reflect on them (&#8220;thinking about thinking&#8221;).</li>
<li><strong>Key Actions:</strong> <strong>Planning</strong> learning, <strong>monitoring</strong> progress, and <strong>evaluating/adjusting</strong> the strategies used.</li>
</ul>
<p>These skills enable an individual to solve complex problems and make effective decisions.</p></p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-05-17T07:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:52:15Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'develop-your-scientific-thinking-skills-in-turkey';
