/roadtostudy.com/en/gpa-calculation-and-academic-success-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 id="turkiyede-gno-nedir-ve-neden-onemlidir" class="wp-block-heading">What is GPA in Turkey and Why is it Important?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">GPA (Grade Point Average), known as GNO in Turkey, is a crucial criterion for measuring students&#8217; academic success. At universities in Turkey, GPA is typically calculated on a scale from 0 to 4.0. Your GPA reflects your performance in your courses and plays a significant role upon graduation. Employers, postgraduate programs, and scholarship applications all take GPA into account. Therefore, maintaining a high GPA provides a significant advantage for students in achieving their career goals.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">The Importance of GPA</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Career Opportunities:</strong> A high GPA gives you an advantage in job and internship applications.</li>
<li><strong>Scholarship Opportunities:</strong> Many scholarship programs offer financial support to students based on their GPA.</li>
<li><strong>Academic Advancement:</strong> A high GPA increases your chances of being accepted into postgraduate programs.</li>
</ul>
<p id="turkiyede-gno-hesaplama-yontemlerigno-hesaplama-derslerde-alinan-notlarin-belirli-bir-formule-gore-agirliklandirilmasi-ile-gerceklestirilir-turkiyedeki-universitelerde-genel-olarak-kullanilan-gno-hesaplama-yontemi-asagidaki-gibidir" class="wp-block-heading">The GPA calculation method generally used in Turkish universities is as follows:</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">GPA Calculation Formula</h3>
<p><b>GNO</b> (Genel Not Ortalaması) or <b>AGNO</b> (Ağırlıklı Genel Not Ortalaması), which translates to Cumulative GPA (CGPA), represents the average of a student&#8217;s performance in <b>all courses</b> taken from their very first semester.</p>
<p>This is a &#8220;weighted&#8221; average because it is calculated using the <b>credit value</b> of each course and the <b>grade point</b> of the letter grade received.</p>
<h2>GPA/CGPA Calculation Formula</h2>
<p>The logic behind the GPA formula is to sum the products of &#8220;credit * grade point&#8221; for all courses and then divide this total by the sum of all credits.</p>
<div class="math-block"><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">GPA (CGPA)</span></span><span class="mrel">=</span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist"><span class=""><span class="mop op-symbol small-op">∑</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord text">Sum of Course Credits</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span><span class=""><span class="mop op-symbol small-op">∑</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord text">Course Credit</span><span class="mbin">×</span><span class="mord text">Letter Grade Point</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>
<div class="math-block"><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>
<h4>Learn the Numerical Grade Points for Letter Grades</h4>
<p>Universities in Turkey generally use a <b>4.00</b> scale. Each letter grade has a numerical equivalent (grade point). These points can vary slightly from one university to another, but the general table is as follows:</p>
<div class="horizontal-scroll-wrapper">
<div class="table-block-component">
<div class="table-block has-export-button">
<div class="table-content not-end-of-paragraph">
<table>
