<p><span style="color: revert; font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, ''Apple Color Emoji'', ''Segoe UI Emoji'', ''Segoe UI Symbol''; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit;">Vous pouvez également consulter notre article sur le </span><a style="font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &#039;Segoe UI&#039;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &#039;Apple Color Emoji&#039;, &#039;Segoe UI Emoji&#039;, &#039;Segoe UI Symbol&#039;; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit;" title="Système de validation des cours et ECTS en Turquie" href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-ders-gecme-akts-sistemi/">Système de validation des cours et ECTS en Turquie</a><span style="color: revert; font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, ''Apple Color Emoji'', ''Segoe UI Emoji'', ''Segoe UI Symbol''; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit;">.</span></div>
<div> </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id="akademik-durumun-gno-uzerindeki-etkileri" class="wp-block-heading">Impact du statut académique sur le GPA</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Le statut académique désigne la performance de l&#8217;étudiant dans ses cours et sa réussite globale tout au long de son parcours éducatif. Ce statut a un impact direct sur le GPA. Voici quelques facteurs qui influencent le GPA des étudiants :</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Facteurs</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Choix des cours :</strong> Suivre des cours très difficiles peut affecter négativement le GPA.</li>
<li><strong>Habitudes de travail :</strong> Une étude régulière et une bonne gestion du temps augmentent la réussite académique.</li>
<li><strong>Systèmes de soutien :</strong> Les services de soutien aux étudiants peuvent aider à surmonter les difficultés académiques.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyedeki-universitelerde-gno-ve-basari-kriterleri" class="wp-block-heading">GPA et critères de réussite dans les universités en Turquie</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Dans les universités turques, le GPA occupe une place importante parmi les critères de réussite des étudiants. Bien que chaque université ait ses propres critères de calcul et d&#8217;évaluation du GPA, les éléments suivants sont généralement pris en compte :</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Critères de réussite</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Notes des cours :</strong> La note obtenue dans chaque cours est un élément fondamental du calcul du GPA.</li>
<li><strong>Valeurs des crédits :</strong> La valeur en crédits de chaque cours est utilisée comme pondération dans le calcul du GPA.</li>
<li><strong>Assiduité :</strong> La présence en cours peut, dans certaines universités, avoir un impact sur le GPA.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="gnonuzu-yukseltmek-icin-ipuclari" class="wp-block-heading">Conseils pour augmenter votre GPA</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Il est important de développer des stratégies pour augmenter votre GPA. Voici quelques conseils qui peuvent vous aider à améliorer votre moyenne :</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Conseils</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Planification des cours :</strong> Équilibrez les cours difficiles avec des cours plus faciles dans votre emploi du temps.</li>
<li><strong>Étude régulière :</strong> Révisez vos connaissances en consacrant un certain temps à l&#8217;étude chaque jour.</li>
<li><strong>Demandez de l&#8217;aide :</strong> N&#8217;hésitez pas à solliciter l&#8217;aide de vos professeurs ou de vos camarades.</li>
<li><strong>Techniques de prise de notes :</strong> Développez une meilleure compréhension en cours en utilisant des méthodes de prise de notes efficaces.</li>
<li><strong>Préparation aux examens :</strong> Préparez-vous à l&#8217;avance pour les examens et testez-vous en faisant des examens blancs.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Foire aux questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Existe-t-il un système de GPA en Turquie ?</h3>
<p>Oui, le système <strong>GNO (Genel Not Ortalaması)</strong> ou <strong>AGNO (Ağırlıklı Genel Not Ortalaması)</strong> utilisé en Turquie est l&#8217;équivalent exact du système américain <strong>GPA (Grade Point Average)</strong> et est généralement calculé sur une échelle de <strong>4.00</strong>.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Comment le GPA (GNO) est-il calculé ?</h3>
<p>Le GPA est calculé en divisant la somme des produits de la <strong>valeur en crédits</strong> de chaque cours par le <strong>coefficient de la note littérale</strong> correspondante, par le <strong>nombre total de crédits</strong> de tous les cours. Formule : ∑(Crédits×Coefficient)​/∑Crédits.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">À quel GPA correspond une moyenne de 85 % ?</h3>
<p>Une moyenne de 85 sur 100 (système de notation sur 100) correspond généralement à une note littérale de <strong>AA</strong> ou <strong>BA</strong>, selon le barème de l&#8217;université. Cela équivaut à un GPA/GNO d&#8217;environ <strong>3.50 à 4.00</strong>.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quel GPA faut-il avoir à l&#8217;université ?</h3>
<p>Pour obtenir son diplôme, un GPA d&#8217;<strong>au moins 2.00</strong> est généralement requis. Pour figurer sur la liste d&#8217;honneur (avec mention), un GPA se situant généralement entre <strong>3.00 et 3.50</strong> ou plus est nécessaire.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-03-14T04:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-06T09:20:30Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'fr' AND "slug" = 'calcul-du-gpa-gno-et-reussite-academique-en-turquie' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","description":"Learn about the academic appeal process in Turkey. Check out our step-by-step guide on how to appeal your exam results and ensure your grade is accurate!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Learn about the academic appeal process in Turkey. Check out our step-by-step guide on how to appeal your exam results and ensure your grade is accurate!","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Learn about the academic appeal process in Turkey. Check out our step-by-step guide on how to appeal your exam results and ensure your grade is accurate!","canonicalPath":"/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/guide-de-la-procedure-de-contestation-des-resultats-dexamen-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/","name":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-12T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-12T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-12T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-12T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Learn about the academic appeal process in Turkey. Check out our step-by-step guide on how to appeal your exam results and ensure your grade is accurate!","name":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p>In Turkey, the <b>exam result appeal process</b> can vary depending on the type of exam (e.g., an internal university exam, an ÖSYM exam). However, the general steps to follow and key points to consider are as follows:</p>
<h2>General Steps in the Appeal Process</h2>
<p>Appealing exam results generally consists of two main stages: an <b>Administrative Appeal to the Relevant Institution</b> and, if the appeal is rejected or the deadline passes without a response, the <b>Legal Route (Administrative Lawsuit)</b>.</p>
<h3>1. Internal Institutional Appeal</h3>
<p>This is typically the first step you should take when you believe your grade has been calculated incorrectly or that there has been a <b>clerical error</b>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>Review the Relevant Regulations:</b> First, check the <b>Academic Regulations</b> or the relevant <b>Exam Guide</b> of the institution where you took the exam (University/Faculty, ÖSYM, etc.). Critical information such as the appeal deadline, procedure, and any fees will be outlined here.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Pay Attention to the Deadline:</b> While appeal deadlines vary by institution, they are typically within <b>3 to 5 business days following the announcement of exam results</b> for universities, and within a short period specified in the relevant guide for ÖSYM. Adhering to these deadlines is mandatory.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Prepare a Formal Letter of Appeal (Dilekçe):</b> You must submit your appeal with a <b>formal letter (dilekçe)</b> that clearly and concisely states the reason for your appeal. For universities, this is typically submitted to the <b>Student Affairs Office</b> or the relevant Department Head. For ÖSYM exams, it is sent to the address and in the format specified by the institution (using a general-purpose petition template).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Pay the Fee if Required:</b> Some institutions, like ÖSYM, may require you to pay a designated <b>fee</b> into a specific bank account for the re-evaluation of your exam paper or documents. You will need to attach the proof of payment to your appeal letter.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Complete the Submission:</b> Submit your letter (with a hand-written signature or via an electronic system) to the specified unit within the deadline. Some universities may require you to initiate the appeal electronically through the <b>Student Information System (OBS)</b> and then personally submit a signed printout.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Evaluation:</b> The institution will typically review your appeal only for <b>clerical errors</b> (e.g., addition mistakes, optical scanning errors, etc.) and will make a decision based on these findings.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. The Administrative Legal Route (Grade Reassessment or Annulment Lawsuit)</h2>
<p>If your internal appeal is rejected or if the institution does not respond within the designated timeframe (an implicit rejection), you have the right to file a <b>Grade Reassessment Lawsuit</b> or an <b>Annulment Lawsuit</b> in the <b>Administrative Court</b>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>Filing Deadline:</b> You must file the lawsuit within <b>60 days</b> from the date you are officially notified of the rejection of your appeal.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Competent Court:</b> The case falls under the jurisdiction of the <b>Administrative Courts</b>. The competent court is the one located in the same city as the institution that made the administrative decision (the university, ÖSYM).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Legal Assistance:</b> The administrative litigation process involves specific and technical legal rules. To avoid a loss of rights, it is <b>highly recommended to seek legal assistance from a lawyer</b>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Expert Examination:</b> The court will typically appoint an <b>expert witness</b> to examine the case file to determine whether your grade was calculated correctly and if there were any errors in the questions or answer key.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Appeal Process for International Students</h2>
<p>If you are an international student studying in Turkey, the process for appealing your exam results is <strong>exactly the same as it is for Turkish citizens</strong>. Your international status does not change the rules or methods of appeal. The path you need to follow depends on which exam you are appealing: an internal university exam (midterm, final) or an exam administered by a central body like ÖSYM?</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Appealing Internal University Exam Results</h3>
<p>If you want to appeal the grades you received in your university courses (midterms, finals, make-up exams), you must first check <strong>your own university&#8217;s Regulations</strong>.</p>
<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Review the Regulations:</strong> Every university has its own <strong>Academic Regulations</strong>. In these regulations, you will find the appeal period (which is usually very short, around <strong>3 to 5 business days</strong> from the announcement of results) and the procedure for submitting an appeal.</li>
<li><strong>Prepare a Formal Letter (Dilekçe):</strong> You need to submit your appeal with a <strong>formal letter (dilekçe)</strong> that clearly states your reason for the appeal. You can often get templates for this letter from the <strong>Student Affairs Department</strong> or the relevant faculty secretary&#8217;s office. Your letter must include your student ID number, the course you are appealing, and the specific reason for your appeal (usually a claim of <strong>clerical error</strong>, such as a calculation or scanning mistake).</li>
<li><strong>Submit Your Application:</strong> You must sign your prepared letter and <strong>submit it in person to the Student Affairs Office</strong> within the deadline. Some modern universities may first ask you to apply electronically via the <strong>Student Information System (OBS)</strong> and then request a hand-signed printout. Don&#8217;t forget to get a document confirming your submission.</li>
<li><strong>Evaluation:</strong> Your appeal will be reviewed by the relevant instructor. Appeals are generally evaluated only to determine if there was an <strong>error in the calculation</strong> of the grade, and you will be notified of the outcome.</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">The Legal Route (Filing a Lawsuit)</h3>
<p>If your internal appeal is rejected or you do not get the desired outcome from the institution, you have the right to <strong>file a lawsuit in the Administrative Court</strong> as a last resort.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Filing Period:</strong> You must file the lawsuit within <strong>60 days</strong> from the date you are officially notified of the institution&#8217;s (university or ÖSYM) decision to reject your appeal.</li>
<li><strong>Legal Support:</strong> Since this stage involves complex legal procedures, it is important to <strong>get professional support from a lawyer</strong>. In such cases, administrative courts typically appoint an <strong>expert witness</strong> to re-examine your exam paper.</li>
</ul>
<p>Remember, as an international student, you are subject to the laws of Turkey, and it is crucial to prepare all necessary documents and letters correctly to avoid any issues due to language barriers.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-05-12T11:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:52:06Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey';
UPDATE "revisions" SET "data" = json_set("data", '$.source_seo', json('{"title":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","description":"Learn about the academic appeal process in Turkey. Check out our step-by-step guide on how to appeal your exam results and ensure your grade is accurate!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Learn about the academic appeal process in Turkey. Check out our step-by-step guide on how to appeal your exam results and ensure your grade is accurate!","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Learn about the academic appeal process in Turkey. Check out our step-by-step guide on how to appeal your exam results and ensure your grade is accurate!","canonicalPath":"/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/guide-de-la-procedure-de-contestation-des-resultats-dexamen-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/","name":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-12T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-12T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-12T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-12T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Learn about the academic appeal process in Turkey. Check out our step-by-step guide on how to appeal your exam results and ensure your grade is accurate!","name":"A Guide to the Exam Result Appeal Process in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p>In Turkey, the <b>exam result appeal process</b> can vary depending on the type of exam (e.g., an internal university exam, an ÖSYM exam). However, the general steps to follow and key points to consider are as follows:</p>
<h2>General Steps in the Appeal Process</h2>
<p>Appealing exam results generally consists of two main stages: an <b>Administrative Appeal to the Relevant Institution</b> and, if the appeal is rejected or the deadline passes without a response, the <b>Legal Route (Administrative Lawsuit)</b>.</p>
<h3>1. Internal Institutional Appeal</h3>
<p>This is typically the first step you should take when you believe your grade has been calculated incorrectly or that there has been a <b>clerical error</b>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>Review the Relevant Regulations:</b> First, check the <b>Academic Regulations</b> or the relevant <b>Exam Guide</b> of the institution where you took the exam (University/Faculty, ÖSYM, etc.). Critical information such as the appeal deadline, procedure, and any fees will be outlined here.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Pay Attention to the Deadline:</b> While appeal deadlines vary by institution, they are typically within <b>3 to 5 business days following the announcement of exam results</b> for universities, and within a short period specified in the relevant guide for ÖSYM. Adhering to these deadlines is mandatory.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Prepare a Formal Letter of Appeal (Dilekçe):</b> You must submit your appeal with a <b>formal letter (dilekçe)</b> that clearly and concisely states the reason for your appeal. For universities, this is typically submitted to the <b>Student Affairs Office</b> or the relevant Department Head. For ÖSYM exams, it is sent to the address and in the format specified by the institution (using a general-purpose petition template).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Pay the Fee if Required:</b> Some institutions, like ÖSYM, may require you to pay a designated <b>fee</b> into a specific bank account for the re-evaluation of your exam paper or documents. You will need to attach the proof of payment to your appeal letter.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Complete the Submission:</b> Submit your letter (with a hand-written signature or via an electronic system) to the specified unit within the deadline. Some universities may require you to initiate the appeal electronically through the <b>Student Information System (OBS)</b> and then personally submit a signed printout.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Evaluation:</b> The institution will typically review your appeal only for <b>clerical errors</b> (e.g., addition mistakes, optical scanning errors, etc.) and will make a decision based on these findings.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. The Administrative Legal Route (Grade Reassessment or Annulment Lawsuit)</h2>
<p>If your internal appeal is rejected or if the institution does not respond within the designated timeframe (an implicit rejection), you have the right to file a <b>Grade Reassessment Lawsuit</b> or an <b>Annulment Lawsuit</b> in the <b>Administrative Court</b>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>Filing Deadline:</b> You must file the lawsuit within <b>60 days</b> from the date you are officially notified of the rejection of your appeal.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Competent Court:</b> The case falls under the jurisdiction of the <b>Administrative Courts</b>. The competent court is the one located in the same city as the institution that made the administrative decision (the university, ÖSYM).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Legal Assistance:</b> The administrative litigation process involves specific and technical legal rules. To avoid a loss of rights, it is <b>highly recommended to seek legal assistance from a lawyer</b>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Expert Examination:</b> The court will typically appoint an <b>expert witness</b> to examine the case file to determine whether your grade was calculated correctly and if there were any errors in the questions or answer key.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Appeal Process for International Students</h2>
<p>If you are an international student studying in Turkey, the process for appealing your exam results is <strong>exactly the same as it is for Turkish citizens</strong>. Your international status does not change the rules or methods of appeal. The path you need to follow depends on which exam you are appealing: an internal university exam (midterm, final) or an exam administered by a central body like ÖSYM?</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Appealing Internal University Exam Results</h3>
<p>If you want to appeal the grades you received in your university courses (midterms, finals, make-up exams), you must first check <strong>your own university&#8217;s Regulations</strong>.</p>
<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Review the Regulations:</strong> Every university has its own <strong>Academic Regulations</strong>. In these regulations, you will find the appeal period (which is usually very short, around <strong>3 to 5 business days</strong> from the announcement of results) and the procedure for submitting an appeal.</li>
<li><strong>Prepare a Formal Letter (Dilekçe):</strong> You need to submit your appeal with a <strong>formal letter (dilekçe)</strong> that clearly states your reason for the appeal. You can often get templates for this letter from the <strong>Student Affairs Department</strong> or the relevant faculty secretary&#8217;s office. Your letter must include your student ID number, the course you are appealing, and the specific reason for your appeal (usually a claim of <strong>clerical error</strong>, such as a calculation or scanning mistake).</li>
<li><strong>Submit Your Application:</strong> You must sign your prepared letter and <strong>submit it in person to the Student Affairs Office</strong> within the deadline. Some modern universities may first ask you to apply electronically via the <strong>Student Information System (OBS)</strong> and then request a hand-signed printout. Don&#8217;t forget to get a document confirming your submission.</li>
<li><strong>Evaluation:</strong> Your appeal will be reviewed by the relevant instructor. Appeals are generally evaluated only to determine if there was an <strong>error in the calculation</strong> of the grade, and you will be notified of the outcome.</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">The Legal Route (Filing a Lawsuit)</h3>
<p>If your internal appeal is rejected or you do not get the desired outcome from the institution, you have the right to <strong>file a lawsuit in the Administrative Court</strong> as a last resort.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Filing Period:</strong> You must file the lawsuit within <strong>60 days</strong> from the date you are officially notified of the institution&#8217;s (university or ÖSYM) decision to reject your appeal.</li>
<li><strong>Legal Support:</strong> Since this stage involves complex legal procedures, it is important to <strong>get professional support from a lawyer</strong>. In such cases, administrative courts typically appoint an <strong>expert witness</strong> to re-examine your exam paper.</li>
</ul>
<p>Remember, as an international student, you are subject to the laws of Turkey, and it is crucial to prepare all necessary documents and letters correctly to avoid any issues due to language barriers.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-05-12T11:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:52:06Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Türkiye''de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","description":"Türkiye''de akademik itiraz süreçlerini öğrenin. Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz için adım adım rehberimizi inceleyin ve hakkınızı savunun!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Türkiye''de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","ogDescription":"Türkiye''de akademik itiraz süreçlerini öğrenin. Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz için adım adım rehberimizi inceleyin ve hakkınızı savunun!","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Türkiye''de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","twitterDescription":"Türkiye''de akademik itiraz süreçlerini öğrenin. Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz için adım adım rehberimizi inceleyin ve hakkınızı savunun!","canonicalPath":"/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/guide-de-la-procedure-de-contestation-des-resultats-dexamen-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"tr","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"tr"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/","name":"Türkiye&#039;de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","datePublished":"2025-09-29T13:59:22+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:41:14+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"tr"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"tr"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Türkiye&#039;de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","keywords":"İtiraz Süreci","datePublished":"2025-09-29T13:59:22+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:41:14+03:00","articleSection":"Akademik Destek ve Başarı","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Türkiye&#039;de akademik itiraz süreçlerini öğrenin. Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz için adım adım rehberimizi inceleyin ve hakkınızı savunun!","name":"Türkiye&#039;de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"tr","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p>Türkiye&#8217;de <b>sınav sonucuna itiraz süreci</b>, itiraz edilen sınavın türüne göre (üniversite içi sınav, ÖSYM sınavı gibi) farklılık gösterebilir. Ancak genel olarak izlenmesi gereken adımlar ve dikkat edilmesi gereken noktalar şunlardır:</p>
<h2>Genel İtiraz Süreci Adımları</h2>
<p>Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz, genellikle iki ana aşamadan oluşur: <b>İlgili Kuruma İdari Başvuru</b> ve sonrasında, ret cevabı alınırsa veya süre geçerse <b>Yargı Yolu (İdari Dava)</b>.</p>
<h3>1. Kurum İçi İtiraz Başvurusu</h3>
<p>Bu, genellikle notunuzun hatalı hesaplandığını veya bir <b>maddi hata</b> olduğunu düşündüğünüzde izlemeniz gereken ilk yoldur.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>İlgili Yönetmeliği İnceleme:</b> Öncelikle, sınava girdiğiniz kurumun (Üniversite/Fakülte, ÖSYM vb.) <b>Eğitim-Öğretim Yönetmeliği</b> veya ilgili <b>Sınav Kılavuzu</b>&#8216;nu kontrol edin. İtiraz süresi, yöntemi ve ücreti gibi kritik bilgiler burada yer alır.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Süreye Dikkat:</b> İtiraz süresi kurumlara göre değişmekle birlikte, üniversitelerde genellikle <b>sınav sonuçlarının ilanını izleyen 3 ila 5 iş günü</b> içinde, ÖSYM&#8217;de ise ilgili kılavuzda belirtilen kısa bir süre içinde yapılır. Bu sürelere uymak zorunludur.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Dilekçe Hazırlama:</b> İtirazınızı, itiraz nedeninizi <b>açık ve anlaşılır</b> bir şekilde belirten bir <b>dilekçe</b> ile yapın. Üniversitelerde genellikle <b>Öğrenci İşleri</b> veya ilgili Bölüm Başkanlığı&#8217;na, ÖSYM sınavlarında ise kurumun belirlediği adres ve formatta (genel amaçlı dilekçe örneği) gönderilir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Gerekiyorsa Ücret Yatırma:</b> ÖSYM gibi bazı kurumlarda, sınav sonucunun veya evrakın incelenmesi için belirlenen bir <b>ücreti</b> ilgili banka hesabına yatırıp dekontu dilekçenize eklemeniz gerekebilir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Başvuruyu Tamamlama:</b> Dilekçenizi (ıslak imzalı veya elektronik sistem üzerinden) belirtilen birime süresi içinde teslim edin. Bazı üniversitelerde <b>Öğrenci Bilgi Sistemi (OBS)</b> üzerinden elektronik başvuru başlatılıp, sonrasında çıktısının bizzat teslimi istenebilir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Değerlendirme:</b> Kurum, itirazınızı genellikle yalnızca <b>maddi hata</b> (toplama hatası, optik okuma hatası, vs.) yönünden inceler ve bir karara bağlar.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. İdari Yargı Yolu (Not Tespit Davası/İptal Davası)</h2>
<p>Kurum içi itirazınız reddedilirse veya kurum, itiraz süresi içinde bir cevap vermezse (zımni ret), <b>İdare Mahkemesi</b>&#8216;nde <b>Not Tespit Davası</b> veya <b>İptal Davası</b> açma hakkınız doğar.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>Dava Açma Süresi:</b> İtirazınızın reddi kararının size tebliğ edilmesinden itibaren <b>60 gün</b> içinde dava açmanız gerekir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Görevli Mahkeme:</b> <b>İdare Mahkemeleri</b> görevlidir. Yetkili mahkeme ise, idari işlemi yapan kurumun (üniversite, ÖSYM) bulunduğu yerdeki mahkemedir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Hukuki Destek:</b> İdari yargılama süreci, özel ve teknik hukuki kurallar içerdiğinden, hak kaybı yaşamamak için <b>bir avukattan hukuki destek almanız</b> şiddetle tavsiye edilir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Bilirkişi İncelemesi:</b> Mahkeme, genellikle dosya kapsamında <b>bilirkişi incelemesi</b> yaptırarak notunuzun doğru hesaplanıp hesaplanmadığını, sorularda veya cevaplarda bir hata olup olmadığını belirler.</p>
</li>
</ul>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Uluslararası Öğrenciler için Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;de okuyan uluslararası bir öğrenciyseniz, sınav sonuçlarına itiraz süreciniz <strong>Türk vatandaşları ile tamamen aynıdır</strong>. Uluslararası statünüz, itirazın kurallarını veya yöntemini değiştirmez. İzlemeniz gereken yol, hangi sınava itiraz ettiğinize bağlıdır: üniversite içi bir sınava mı (vize, final) yoksa ÖSYM gibi merkezi bir kurumun sınavına mı?</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Üniversite İçi Sınav Sonuçlarına İtiraz</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Üniversitenizdeki derslerden aldığınız notlara (ara sınav, final, bütünleme) itiraz etmek istiyorsanız, öncelikle <strong>kendi üniversitenizin Yönetmeliği&#8217;ni</strong> kontrol etmelisiniz.</p>



<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Yönetmeliği İnceleyin:</strong> Her üniversitenin kendi <strong>Eğitim-Öğretim Yönetmeliği</strong> bulunur. Bu yönetmelikte, sınav sonuçlarının ilan edilmesinden itibaren itiraz için tanınan süreyi (genellikle çok kısadır, <strong>3 ila 5 iş günü</strong> civarındadır) ve itirazın nasıl yapılacağını bulacaksınız.</li>



<li><strong>Dilekçe Hazırlayın:</strong> İtirazınızı, itiraz nedeninizi açıkça belirten bir <strong>dilekçe</strong> ile yapmanız gerekir. Bu dilekçe örneklerini genellikle <strong>Öğrenci İşleri Daire Başkanlığı&#8217;ndan</strong> ya da ilgili fakülte sekreterliğinden temin edebilirsiniz. Dilekçenizde öğrenci numaranız, itiraz ettiğiniz ders ve asıl itiraz gerekçeniz (genellikle <strong>maddi hata</strong> yani toplama ya da okuma hatası iddiası) yer almalıdır.</li>



<li><strong>Başvurunuzu Yapın:</strong> Hazırladığınız dilekçeyi imzalayarak süresi içinde <strong>Öğrenci İşleri&#8217;ne bizzat teslim etmelisiniz</strong>. Bazı modern üniversiteler, öncelikle <strong>Öğrenci Bilgi Sistemi (OBS)</strong> üzerinden elektronik başvuru yapmanızı isteyip, ardından ıslak imzalı çıktısını talep edebilir. Başvurunuzun kaydını gösteren belgeyi almayı unutmayın.</li>



<li><strong>Değerlendirme:</strong> İtirazınız ilgili öğretim görevlisi tarafından incelenir. İtirazlar genellikle yalnızca notun <strong>hesaplanmasında hata olup olmadığı</strong> yönünden değerlendirilir ve sonucu size bildirilir.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">İdari Yargı Yolu (Dava Açma)</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğer kurum içi itirazınız reddedilirse veya kurumdan istediğiniz sonucu alamazsanız, son çare olarak <strong>İdare Mahkemesi&#8217;nde dava açma</strong> hakkınız vardır.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Dava Süresi:</strong> Kurumun (üniversite ya da ÖSYM) itirazınızı reddetme kararının size tebliğ edilmesinden itibaren <strong>60 gün</strong> içinde dava açmanız gerekir.</li>



<li><strong>Hukuki Destek:</strong> Bu aşama karmaşık hukuki prosedürler gerektirdiğinden, <strong>bir avukattan profesyonel destek almanız</strong> önemlidir. İdare mahkemeleri bu tür davalarda genellikle sınav kağıdınızı incelemek üzere <strong>bilirkişi</strong> atar.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Unutmayın, uluslararası bir öğrenci olarak Türkiye&#8217;deki yasalara tabi olursunuz ve bu süreçte dil engeli yaşamamak için gerekli belgeleri ve dilekçeleri doğru şekilde hazırlamak büyük önem taşır.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-09-29T10:59:22Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:41:14Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'tr' AND "slug" = 'turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci';
UPDATE "revisions" SET "data" = json_set("data", '$.source_seo', json('{"title":"Türkiye''de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","description":"Türkiye''de akademik itiraz süreçlerini öğrenin. Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz için adım adım rehberimizi inceleyin ve hakkınızı savunun!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Türkiye''de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","ogDescription":"Türkiye''de akademik itiraz süreçlerini öğrenin. Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz için adım adım rehberimizi inceleyin ve hakkınızı savunun!","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Türkiye''de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","twitterDescription":"Türkiye''de akademik itiraz süreçlerini öğrenin. Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz için adım adım rehberimizi inceleyin ve hakkınızı savunun!","canonicalPath":"/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/guide-de-la-procedure-de-contestation-des-resultats-dexamen-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"tr","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"tr"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/","name":"Türkiye&#039;de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","datePublished":"2025-09-29T13:59:22+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:41:14+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"tr"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"tr"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Türkiye&#039;de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","keywords":"İtiraz Süreci","datePublished":"2025-09-29T13:59:22+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:41:14+03:00","articleSection":"Akademik Destek ve Başarı","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Türkiye&#039;de akademik itiraz süreçlerini öğrenin. Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz için adım adım rehberimizi inceleyin ve hakkınızı savunun!","name":"Türkiye&#039;de Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci Rehberi","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"tr","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p>Türkiye&#8217;de <b>sınav sonucuna itiraz süreci</b>, itiraz edilen sınavın türüne göre (üniversite içi sınav, ÖSYM sınavı gibi) farklılık gösterebilir. Ancak genel olarak izlenmesi gereken adımlar ve dikkat edilmesi gereken noktalar şunlardır:</p>
<h2>Genel İtiraz Süreci Adımları</h2>
<p>Sınav sonuçlarına itiraz, genellikle iki ana aşamadan oluşur: <b>İlgili Kuruma İdari Başvuru</b> ve sonrasında, ret cevabı alınırsa veya süre geçerse <b>Yargı Yolu (İdari Dava)</b>.</p>
<h3>1. Kurum İçi İtiraz Başvurusu</h3>
<p>Bu, genellikle notunuzun hatalı hesaplandığını veya bir <b>maddi hata</b> olduğunu düşündüğünüzde izlemeniz gereken ilk yoldur.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>İlgili Yönetmeliği İnceleme:</b> Öncelikle, sınava girdiğiniz kurumun (Üniversite/Fakülte, ÖSYM vb.) <b>Eğitim-Öğretim Yönetmeliği</b> veya ilgili <b>Sınav Kılavuzu</b>&#8216;nu kontrol edin. İtiraz süresi, yöntemi ve ücreti gibi kritik bilgiler burada yer alır.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Süreye Dikkat:</b> İtiraz süresi kurumlara göre değişmekle birlikte, üniversitelerde genellikle <b>sınav sonuçlarının ilanını izleyen 3 ila 5 iş günü</b> içinde, ÖSYM&#8217;de ise ilgili kılavuzda belirtilen kısa bir süre içinde yapılır. Bu sürelere uymak zorunludur.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Dilekçe Hazırlama:</b> İtirazınızı, itiraz nedeninizi <b>açık ve anlaşılır</b> bir şekilde belirten bir <b>dilekçe</b> ile yapın. Üniversitelerde genellikle <b>Öğrenci İşleri</b> veya ilgili Bölüm Başkanlığı&#8217;na, ÖSYM sınavlarında ise kurumun belirlediği adres ve formatta (genel amaçlı dilekçe örneği) gönderilir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Gerekiyorsa Ücret Yatırma:</b> ÖSYM gibi bazı kurumlarda, sınav sonucunun veya evrakın incelenmesi için belirlenen bir <b>ücreti</b> ilgili banka hesabına yatırıp dekontu dilekçenize eklemeniz gerekebilir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Başvuruyu Tamamlama:</b> Dilekçenizi (ıslak imzalı veya elektronik sistem üzerinden) belirtilen birime süresi içinde teslim edin. Bazı üniversitelerde <b>Öğrenci Bilgi Sistemi (OBS)</b> üzerinden elektronik başvuru başlatılıp, sonrasında çıktısının bizzat teslimi istenebilir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Değerlendirme:</b> Kurum, itirazınızı genellikle yalnızca <b>maddi hata</b> (toplama hatası, optik okuma hatası, vs.) yönünden inceler ve bir karara bağlar.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. İdari Yargı Yolu (Not Tespit Davası/İptal Davası)</h2>
<p>Kurum içi itirazınız reddedilirse veya kurum, itiraz süresi içinde bir cevap vermezse (zımni ret), <b>İdare Mahkemesi</b>&#8216;nde <b>Not Tespit Davası</b> veya <b>İptal Davası</b> açma hakkınız doğar.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>Dava Açma Süresi:</b> İtirazınızın reddi kararının size tebliğ edilmesinden itibaren <b>60 gün</b> içinde dava açmanız gerekir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Görevli Mahkeme:</b> <b>İdare Mahkemeleri</b> görevlidir. Yetkili mahkeme ise, idari işlemi yapan kurumun (üniversite, ÖSYM) bulunduğu yerdeki mahkemedir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Hukuki Destek:</b> İdari yargılama süreci, özel ve teknik hukuki kurallar içerdiğinden, hak kaybı yaşamamak için <b>bir avukattan hukuki destek almanız</b> şiddetle tavsiye edilir.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Bilirkişi İncelemesi:</b> Mahkeme, genellikle dosya kapsamında <b>bilirkişi incelemesi</b> yaptırarak notunuzun doğru hesaplanıp hesaplanmadığını, sorularda veya cevaplarda bir hata olup olmadığını belirler.</p>
</li>
</ul>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Uluslararası Öğrenciler için Sınav Sonucuna İtiraz Süreci</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye&#8217;de okuyan uluslararası bir öğrenciyseniz, sınav sonuçlarına itiraz süreciniz <strong>Türk vatandaşları ile tamamen aynıdır</strong>. Uluslararası statünüz, itirazın kurallarını veya yöntemini değiştirmez. İzlemeniz gereken yol, hangi sınava itiraz ettiğinize bağlıdır: üniversite içi bir sınava mı (vize, final) yoksa ÖSYM gibi merkezi bir kurumun sınavına mı?</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Üniversite İçi Sınav Sonuçlarına İtiraz</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Üniversitenizdeki derslerden aldığınız notlara (ara sınav, final, bütünleme) itiraz etmek istiyorsanız, öncelikle <strong>kendi üniversitenizin Yönetmeliği&#8217;ni</strong> kontrol etmelisiniz.</p>



<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Yönetmeliği İnceleyin:</strong> Her üniversitenin kendi <strong>Eğitim-Öğretim Yönetmeliği</strong> bulunur. Bu yönetmelikte, sınav sonuçlarının ilan edilmesinden itibaren itiraz için tanınan süreyi (genellikle çok kısadır, <strong>3 ila 5 iş günü</strong> civarındadır) ve itirazın nasıl yapılacağını bulacaksınız.</li>



<li><strong>Dilekçe Hazırlayın:</strong> İtirazınızı, itiraz nedeninizi açıkça belirten bir <strong>dilekçe</strong> ile yapmanız gerekir. Bu dilekçe örneklerini genellikle <strong>Öğrenci İşleri Daire Başkanlığı&#8217;ndan</strong> ya da ilgili fakülte sekreterliğinden temin edebilirsiniz. Dilekçenizde öğrenci numaranız, itiraz ettiğiniz ders ve asıl itiraz gerekçeniz (genellikle <strong>maddi hata</strong> yani toplama ya da okuma hatası iddiası) yer almalıdır.</li>



<li><strong>Başvurunuzu Yapın:</strong> Hazırladığınız dilekçeyi imzalayarak süresi içinde <strong>Öğrenci İşleri&#8217;ne bizzat teslim etmelisiniz</strong>. Bazı modern üniversiteler, öncelikle <strong>Öğrenci Bilgi Sistemi (OBS)</strong> üzerinden elektronik başvuru yapmanızı isteyip, ardından ıslak imzalı çıktısını talep edebilir. Başvurunuzun kaydını gösteren belgeyi almayı unutmayın.</li>



<li><strong>Değerlendirme:</strong> İtirazınız ilgili öğretim görevlisi tarafından incelenir. İtirazlar genellikle yalnızca notun <strong>hesaplanmasında hata olup olmadığı</strong> yönünden değerlendirilir ve sonucu size bildirilir.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">İdari Yargı Yolu (Dava Açma)</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğer kurum içi itirazınız reddedilirse veya kurumdan istediğiniz sonucu alamazsanız, son çare olarak <strong>İdare Mahkemesi&#8217;nde dava açma</strong> hakkınız vardır.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Dava Süresi:</strong> Kurumun (üniversite ya da ÖSYM) itirazınızı reddetme kararının size tebliğ edilmesinden itibaren <strong>60 gün</strong> içinde dava açmanız gerekir.</li>



<li><strong>Hukuki Destek:</strong> Bu aşama karmaşık hukuki prosedürler gerektirdiğinden, <strong>bir avukattan profesyonel destek almanız</strong> önemlidir. İdare mahkemeleri bu tür davalarda genellikle sınav kağıdınızı incelemek üzere <strong>bilirkişi</strong> atar.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Unutmayın, uluslararası bir öğrenci olarak Türkiye&#8217;deki yasalara tabi olursunuz ve bu süreçte dil engeli yaşamamak için gerekli belgeleri ve dilekçeleri doğru şekilde hazırlamak büyük önem taşır.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-09-29T10:59:22Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:41:14Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'tr' AND "slug" = 'turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Panduan Proses Banding Hasil Ujian di Turki - RoadtoStudy","description":"Pelajari proses banding akademik di Turki. Simak panduan langkah demi langkah kami untuk mengajukan banding atas hasil ujian dan memperjuangkan hak Anda!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Panduan Proses Banding Hasil Ujian di Turki - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Pelajari proses banding akademik di Turki. Simak panduan langkah demi langkah kami untuk mengajukan banding atas hasil ujian dan memperjuangkan hak Anda!","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Panduan Proses Banding Hasil Ujian di Turki - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Pelajari proses banding akademik di Turki. Simak panduan langkah demi langkah kami untuk mengajukan banding atas hasil ujian dan memperjuangkan hak Anda!","canonicalPath":"/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/a-guide-to-the-exam-result-appeal-process-in-turkey/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/guide-de-la-procedure-de-contestation-des-resultats-dexamen-en-turquie/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"id","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"id"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/","name":"Panduan Proses Banding Hasil Ujian di Turki - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-24T12:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-24T12:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"id"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/id/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/id/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"id"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Panduan Proses Banding Hasil Ujian di Turki - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-24T12:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-24T12:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Dukungan dan Kesuksesan Akademik","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/id/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Pelajari proses banding akademik di Turki. Simak panduan langkah demi langkah kami untuk mengajukan banding atas hasil ujian dan memperjuangkan hak Anda!","name":"Panduan Proses Banding Hasil Ujian di Turki - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"id","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/id/panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p>Di Turki, <b>proses banding hasil ujian</b> dapat berbeda tergantung pada jenis ujian yang dibanding (seperti ujian internal universitas, ujian ÖSYM). Namun, secara umum, berikut adalah langkah-langkah yang harus diikuti dan poin-poin yang perlu diperhatikan:</p>
<h2>Langkah-langkah Umum Proses Banding</h2>
<p>Banding atas hasil ujian umumnya terdiri dari dua tahap utama: <b>Pengajuan Administratif ke Institusi Terkait</b> dan, jika permohonan ditolak atau tidak ada jawaban dalam batas waktu, <b>Jalur Hukum (Gugatan Administratif)</b>.</p>
<h3>1. Pengajuan Banding Internal Institusi</h3>
<p>Ini adalah jalur pertama yang harus Anda ambil, terutama jika Anda merasa nilai Anda salah dihitung atau terdapat <b>kesalahan material</b>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>Periksa Peraturan Terkait:</b> Pertama, periksa <b>Peraturan Pendidikan dan Pengajaran</b> atau <b>Panduan Ujian</b> yang relevan dari institusi tempat Anda mengikuti ujian (Universitas/Fakultas, ÖSYM, dll.). Informasi penting seperti batas waktu banding, prosedur, dan biaya tercantum di sana.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Perhatikan Batas Waktu:</b> Batas waktu banding bervariasi antar institusi, tetapi di universitas biasanya dalam <b>3 hingga 5 hari kerja setelah pengumuman hasil ujian</b>, sedangkan untuk ÖSYM, batas waktunya singkat dan ditentukan dalam panduan terkait. Mematuhi batas waktu ini adalah wajib.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Siapkan Surat Permohonan:</b> Ajukan banding Anda dengan <b>surat permohonan (dilekçe)</b> yang menjelaskan alasan banding Anda secara <b>jelas dan lugas</b>. Di universitas, surat ini biasanya diserahkan ke <b>Bagian Kemahasiswaan</b> atau Kantor Ketua Jurusan terkait. Untuk ujian ÖSYM, surat dikirim ke alamat dan dalam format yang ditentukan oleh lembaga tersebut (contoh surat permohonan umum).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Bayar Biaya Jika Diperlukan:</b> Di beberapa institusi seperti ÖSYM, Anda mungkin perlu membayar <b>biaya</b> yang telah ditentukan untuk peninjauan hasil ujian atau dokumen. Anda harus menyetorkannya ke rekening bank yang ditunjuk dan melampirkan bukti pembayaran pada surat permohonan Anda.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Selesaikan Pengajuan:</b> Serahkan surat permohonan Anda (bertanda tangan basah atau melalui sistem elektronik) ke unit yang ditunjuk dalam batas waktu yang ditentukan. Beberapa universitas mungkin meminta Anda untuk memulai pengajuan secara elektronik melalui <b>Sistem Informasi Mahasiswa (OBS)</b>, lalu menyerahkan versi cetak yang sudah ditandatangani secara langsung.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Evaluasi:</b> Institusi biasanya akan meninjau banding Anda hanya dari aspek <b>kesalahan material</b> (misalnya, kesalahan penjumlahan, kesalahan pembacaan optik, dll.) dan kemudian membuat keputusan.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. Jalur Hukum Administratif (Gugatan Penetapan Nilai/Gugatan Pembatalan)</h2>
<p>Jika banding internal Anda ditolak atau institusi tidak memberikan jawaban dalam batas waktu (penolakan implisit), Anda berhak mengajukan <b>Gugatan Penetapan Nilai</b> atau <b>Gugatan Pembatalan</b> di <b>Pengadilan Administratif</b>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><b>Batas Waktu Pengajuan Gugatan:</b> Anda harus mengajukan gugatan dalam waktu <b>60 hari</b> sejak Anda menerima pemberitahuan resmi mengenai penolakan banding Anda.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Pengadilan yang Berwenang:</b> Gugatan ini ditangani oleh <b>Pengadilan Administratif</b>. Pengadilan yang berwenang adalah pengadilan yang berlokasi di tempat institusi yang mengeluarkan keputusan administratif tersebut (universitas, ÖSYM) berada.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Bantuan Hukum:</b> Karena proses peradilan administratif melibatkan aturan hukum yang khusus dan teknis, sangat disarankan agar Anda <b>mendapatkan bantuan hukum dari seorang pengacara</b> untuk menghindari kehilangan hak Anda.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><b>Pemeriksaan oleh Ahli:</b> Pengadilan biasanya akan menunjuk <b>pemeriksaan oleh ahli</b> untuk menentukan apakah nilai Anda dihitung dengan benar dan apakah ada kesalahan dalam soal atau kunci jawaban.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Proses Banding Hasil Ujian untuk Mahasiswa Internasional</h2>
<p>Jika Anda adalah mahasiswa internasional yang belajar di Turki, proses banding hasil ujian Anda <strong>sepenuhnya sama dengan warga negara Turki</strong>. Status internasional Anda tidak mengubah aturan atau metode banding. Jalur yang harus Anda ikuti bergantung pada ujian mana yang Anda banding: apakah ujian internal universitas (seperti ujian tengah semester, ujian akhir) atau ujian dari lembaga terpusat seperti ÖSYM?</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Banding Hasil Ujian Internal Universitas</h3>
<p>Jika Anda ingin mengajukan banding atas nilai yang Anda terima dari mata kuliah di universitas Anda (ujian tengah semester, ujian akhir, ujian perbaikan), Anda harus terlebih dahulu memeriksa <strong>Peraturan universitas Anda sendiri</strong>.</p>
<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Periksa Peraturan:</strong> Setiap universitas memiliki <strong>Peraturan Pendidikan dan Pengajaran</strong> sendiri. Dalam peraturan ini, Anda akan menemukan informasi tentang batas waktu yang diberikan untuk banding setelah hasil ujian diumumkan (biasanya sangat singkat, sekitar <strong>3 hingga 5 hari kerja</strong>) dan bagaimana cara mengajukan banding.</li>
<li><strong>Siapkan Surat Permohonan:</strong> Anda harus mengajukan banding dengan <strong>surat permohonan (dilekçe)</strong> yang dengan jelas menyatakan alasan banding Anda. Anda biasanya bisa mendapatkan contoh surat ini dari <strong>Kantor Urusan Kemahasiswaan</strong> atau sekretariat fakultas terkait. Surat permohonan Anda harus mencantumkan nomor mahasiswa Anda, mata kuliah yang Anda banding, dan alasan utama banding (biasanya klaim adanya <strong>kesalahan material</strong>, yaitu kesalahan penjumlahan atau pembacaan).</li>
<li><strong>Ajukan Permohonan Anda:</strong> Anda harus <strong>menyerahkan langsung surat permohonan yang telah Anda tandatangani ke Bagian Kemahasiswaan</strong> dalam batas waktu yang ditentukan. Beberapa universitas modern mungkin meminta Anda untuk mengajukan permohonan secara elektronik terlebih dahulu melalui <strong>Sistem Informasi Mahasiswa (OBS)</strong>, kemudian meminta versi cetak yang bertanda tangan basah. Jangan lupa untuk meminta bukti bahwa permohonan Anda telah diterima.</li>
<li><strong>Evaluasi:</strong> Banding Anda akan ditinjau oleh dosen yang bersangkutan. Banding biasanya hanya dievaluasi dari aspek <strong>apakah ada kesalahan dalam perhitungan</strong> nilai, dan hasilnya akan diberitahukan kepada Anda.</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Jalur Hukum Administratif (Mengajukan Gugatan)</h3>
<p>Jika banding internal Anda ditolak atau Anda tidak mendapatkan hasil yang diinginkan dari institusi, sebagai upaya terakhir, Anda memiliki hak untuk <strong>mengajukan gugatan di Pengadilan Administratif</strong>.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Batas Waktu Gugatan:</strong> Anda harus mengajukan gugatan dalam waktu <strong>60 hari</strong> sejak keputusan penolakan banding dari institusi (universitas atau ÖSYM) diberitahukan secara resmi kepada Anda.</li>
<li><strong>Bantuan Hukum:</strong> Karena tahap ini memerlukan prosedur hukum yang rumit, penting bagi Anda untuk <strong>mendapatkan bantuan profesional dari seorang pengacara</strong>. Dalam kasus seperti ini, pengadilan administratif biasanya akan menunjuk seorang <strong>ahli</strong> untuk memeriksa lembar ujian Anda.</li>
</ul>
<p>Ingat, sebagai mahasiswa internasional, Anda tunduk pada hukum di Turki, dan sangat penting untuk mempersiapkan dokumen serta surat permohonan yang diperlukan dengan benar untuk menghindari kendala bahasa selama proses ini.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-03-24T09:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-14T16:04:15Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'id' AND "slug" = 'panduan-proses-banding-hasil-ujian-di-turki';
