Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/academic-discipline-processes-and-regulations-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/academic-discipline-processes-and-regulations-in-turkey/","name":"Academic Discipline Processes and Regulations in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-12T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-12T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Academic Discipline Processes and Regulations in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-12T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-12T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover the academic disciplinary processes and regulations in Turkey. Read our article now to learn more!","name":"Academic Discipline Processes and Regulations in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/academic-discipline-processes-and-regulations-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/academic-discipline-processes-and-regulations-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/academic-discipline-processes-and-regulations-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 id="turkiyede-egitimde-akademik-disiplin-nedir" class="wp-block-heading">What is Academic Discipline in Turkish Education?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Academic discipline is the set of rules and regulations that students and academic staff must adhere to at universities. In Turkey, academic discipline is shaped by regulations determined by the <a href="https://www.yok.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Council of Higher Education (YÖK)</a>. These regulations govern students&#8217; academic achievements, behavior, and overall educational life. Students are expected to adhere to certain standards in areas such as academic integrity, attendance, and exam rules.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Examples:</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Academic Integrity:</strong> Behaviors such as cheating or plagiarism are among the situations that require disciplinary action.</li>
<li><strong>Attendance:</strong> The rate of absence in a particular course can affect a student&#8217;s success and may initiate a disciplinary process.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">On this topic, you can also benefit from our article <a title="Academic Appeals and the Process for Contesting Exam Results in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-sinav-sonucuna-itiraz-sureci/">Academic Appeals and the Process for Contesting Exam Results in Turkey</a>.</p>
<h2 id="uluslararasi-ogrenciler-icin-turkiyedeki-akademik-disiplin-surecleri" class="wp-block-heading">Academic Disciplinary Processes in Turkey for International Students</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students are subject to the academic disciplinary processes in Turkey. However, these processes are applied flexibly, taking into account the cultural differences of the students. YÖK has made various arrangements to facilitate the educational lives of international students.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Cultural Differences:</strong> Universities organize orientation programs to help students from different countries adapt to the academic disciplinary rules in Turkey.</li>
<li><strong>Language Support:</strong> Language support programs are offered to international students studying in Turkey, making it easier for them to understand academic rules.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyedeki-universitelerin-akademik-disiplin-politikalari" class="wp-block-heading">Academic Discipline Policies of Universities in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each university has its own academic discipline policies. These policies are created in accordance with the general framework set by YÖK and are tailored to the specific needs of each university.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Disciplinary Regulations:</strong> Each university establishes its own disciplinary regulations. For example, the disciplinary regulations of Boğaziçi Üniversitesi define student conduct and disciplinary penalties in detail.</li>
<li><strong>Disciplinary Boards:</strong> Disciplinary boards at universities are authorized to evaluate violations and apply penalties. These boards strive to make a fair decision by hearing the students&#8217; defenses.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="yuksekogretim-kurumlari-ogrenci-disiplin-yonetmeligi-yururlukte-mi" class="wp-block-heading">Is the Higher Education Institutions Student Disciplinary Regulation in Effect?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, the student disciplinary regulation for higher education institutions in Turkey is in effect. This regulation governs the academic and social lives of students and specifies the penalties to be applied in cases of disciplinary violations.</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Current Regulations:</strong> The regulations determined by YÖK are integrated into each university&#8217;s own disciplinary regulations. For example, there are clear rules regarding topics like attendance and compliance with exam rules.</li>
<li><strong>Penalties:</strong> The penalties that students may receive as a result of disciplinary violations include sanctions such as warnings, reprimands, temporary or permanent suspension.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="yuksekogretim-kurumlarinda-disiplin-cezalari-nelerdir" class="wp-block-heading">What are the Disciplinary Penalties in Higher Education Institutions?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Disciplinary penalties are an important element in regulating the academic and social lives of students. The disciplinary penalties applied in higher education institutions in Turkey are generally as follows:</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Penalties:</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Warning:</strong> A penalty given for minor violations, aimed at correcting the student&#8217;s behavior.</li>
<li><strong>Reprimand:</strong> Applied for more serious violations and emphasizes the gravity of the student&#8217;s behavior.</li>
<li><strong>Temporary Suspension:</strong> The removal of a student from the educational institution for a specific period. It is generally applied for more serious disciplinary violations.</li>
<li><strong>Expulsion:</strong> The most severe disciplinary penalty, involving the permanent removal of the student from the educational institution.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<div id="model-response-message-contentr_31a04f7e9590cf23" class="markdown markdown-main-panel stronger enable-updated-hr-color" dir="ltr">
<h3>Is the higher education institutions&#8217; student disciplinary regulation in effect?</h3>
<p>The <b>Higher Education Institutions Student Disciplinary Regulation</b> has been repealed. Student disciplinary matters are now directly handled under the provisions of <b>Article 54 of the Higher Education Law No. 2547</b>.</p>
<h3>How many members are on an academic disciplinary board?</h3>
<p>The number of members on a disciplinary board for academic staff varies depending on the staff&#8217;s position and unit. For example, the Disciplinary Board for academic staff affiliated with the Rectorate usually consists of <b>four professors chaired by a Vice-Rector</b>.</p>
<h3>What are the disciplinary penalties in higher education institutions?</h3>
<p>The disciplinary penalties applied to students are as follows: <b>Warning, Reprimand, Suspension for One Week to One Month, Suspension for One Semester, Suspension for Two Semesters</b>, and the most severe, <b>Expulsion from the Higher Education Institution</b>.</p>
</div>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-05-12T07:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:52:05Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'academic-discipline-processes-and-regulations-in-turkey';
